 a strong trade unionist and that - trade unions were formed and give - make better conditions for the people and I think that was his outlook. But he was never violent in any way, as I say, he was very quiet and - in his way. But he was certainly a man w
ho voted Labour, \lquote cos you remember we had Jimmy Thomas in Derby in those days, James Thomas and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15021746  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 - he was quite good in his early days 
\lquote til he got mixed up with the other side in later years.
