 a sort of passing interest, she was interested in what they were - if they were going to try and - in the days when Labour were coming into power - to make better houses and better facilities and particular the health service that she was on about. She t
alked about the women of those days who had all kinds of illnesses and so on and they couldn\rquote t afford a doctor and died early as a result of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did she have any political views when you were a young child, before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well she said - your grandad\rquote s a strong Liberal, a Radical Liberal, which of course in these days we\rquote 
