\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And at the club with the Oddfellows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And of course they
 used to pay out a small sick pay you know and he was a sick visitor at times, visiting them and taking them this little bit of cash and that kind of thing, to members of the - the Oddfellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So he would get to know quite a few of them in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How often do you think people used to come go your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Mainly at holiday times. Easter, Christmas - Whitsun, so on, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 When they came would they have anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. Yes. Had a meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It was normally at holiday times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you say the friends }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 invited}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  in were your mother\rquote s friends or your father\rquote s friends or both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Both of them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there any friends who called in casually without invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well they\rquote 
d probably be neighbours. Fairly near neighbours who would call round, inquire after your health and if they knew they could help themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 But it wouldn\rquote t be anything regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It would be as and when people felt like popping in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. That\rquote s right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - yes, particularly when the children were beginning to grow up. But I think my mother regard
ed as her first duty at home when they were young, up to the age of ten, eleven, twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 We\rquote 
re told that people in those days made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well I think it was mainly a friendly chat, a cup of tea and that kind of thing those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was there any music attached to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, in - if the - if the parents had got a piano or someone in the family could play the piano, holiday time - Chri
stmas in particular - you might go and spend and hour and have an hours singing or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What about games, did they play games with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, not generally, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Many people divide society into diff
erent social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, there was, especially when you come to say the foreman or managers of works in the area and that kind of thing, who lived
 round there. A number of small industries and that round there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What were the different sort of classes then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well the foremen and those people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Which classed would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - generally the working class. The - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well generally working class people. Yes. There was an - an odd exception occasionally }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 you\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  find a - a friendly publican, if anyone of his customers were ill or - of course in those days they couldn\rquote 
t afford to go out and drink every night in any case, probably }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 weekend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 was the only time and not always then I mean, have a small drink of beer which was much heaper of course in those days but me - me mother didn\rquote t, me father did, he used to go down to the local and chat to his friends and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Your sort of family belonged generally speaking to the working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What sort of people belonged to the other classes, you mentioned foremen and people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you put them in the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, in those days, yes, generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What other people would belong to the middle class then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well as I say in my early days you\rquote d find the - foremen and their wives, again some 
went to a certain - certain religious - church and that kind of thing. But there was a generally a friendly feeling - generally around there, if were people ill - the neighbours would try and find out what they could do to help, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 In your part of Derby you wouldn\rquote t have many of the \'85..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 Aristocracy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 ? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Big employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well the big employers lived on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 outskirts}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 , in their sort of mansion. Used to drive \lquote em out in the old }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 coach}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 and the old cabs in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And they would be regarded as upper class would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, I don\rquote t think so, I thought we tried to be friendly with them all if they happened to be funny we\rquote 
d have to probably say all right, kill \lquote em off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 To - well particularly the schoolmaster, the schoolteachers and the Vicar and those people. And to the ladies.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was there anyone you called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 sir}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Not often, no. No. Used to be mister generally and - probably at school they\rquote d call the headmaster sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes. I say, neighbours or relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who do you think would be important in hour particular area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well it\rquote s - it\rquote s not easy to say is it - I say the people who were the owners of the firms and that kind of thing, and the 
Vicars, school headmaster and the school teachers, yes, the teaching staff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you ever come into contact with them apart from the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Occasionally. Yes, if there was some sort of function on at the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 But did you come into contact with the Vicars and the employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, not generally, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Why do you think they were considered important, was it merely because of their position?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh I think so. Yes, I think it was the fact that they employed people and the p
eople had to be grateful for being employed by them I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who did shopkeepers generally associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Generally very friendly. Very friendly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Friendly with the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. You see, they - they relied upon it for their trade of course. They were generally very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Can you remember much about the clergy, who they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - they had a separate Vicarage down in the area with some grounds and later they had a bowling green built down there in
 later years and all that kind of thing. And a lot of the people - working in the engineering, and other firms round there, they played on this - church vicarage bowling green, things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did teachers generally mix in the community or were they separate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 They - well - they mixed - they didn\rquote t become too - what shall I say - too familiar with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would there be any farmers in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, quite a lot of farmers, yes. Some of them were friendly but - some of them were friendly, farmers. They seemed -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Employers were further }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 a field}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you get the impression that the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 e separate groups, clergy, teachers, farmers, employers, kept to themselves or did they mix generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Probably I should think they might, yes, they\rquote d mix together in their own groups, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What sort of people would you say went to the church and what soft of people went to the chapel, was there any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - much the same class of people down there i
n the main, particularly the artisan type of person, the skilled - the more skilled type of person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did they go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 To the churches and - and chapel. And - a number of the labouring section as well but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 They both had a cross section then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living or would you say that there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, there were different groups and - generally the
y were good, they looked after the children, they kept their homes reasonably well, there\rquote d be a few - go off the rails occasionally and there\rquote d be some neglect in those days, but nothing like we\rquote ve seen in - in later years. And that
\rquote s when I think some of the neighbours got annoyed if they found that certain families were not - being helpful and looking after the - their families as they should do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 But did they have the same standard of living generally speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Mainly, and probably they\rquote d be a
 bit below the skilled people - the artisan type you see, in their income I mean and therefore their conditions were not so good, although none - none of them were really good, but - I think the skilled person in the main began to try to improve their out
look and everything for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 family\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  sake and for the communities sake.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I don\rquote t think so, occasionally - may have been occasional people who did but generally they were a co-operative type of class. They
\rquote d }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 meet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  with people, they\rquote  try to help people. If somebody made a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 nuisance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  of themselves then they hadn\rquote t got any room for them and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there some families that were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 To some extent but not general. Not general.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Generally I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 ocial class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, no, I think she\rquote 
d got that sort of friends and neighbours attitude and - appreciated help and was glad to give help if she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 But she\rquote d had this radical upbringing anyway hadn\rquote t she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So she certainly couldn\rquote t feel inferior to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you say her sympathies lay with the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, generally, yes, yes. A neighbourly sort of outlook to the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 There was - there was the odd cases - a small minority of cases I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Can you remember anyone who did jump on the scale?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Can\rquote t remember their na
mes off hand but I can remember there were that type of person and they - they were described as getting a bit snooty or a bit - in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who would it be, what sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well they\rquote 
d probably be again the people who - some - probably some people - like the shopkeepers or the - local - religious people, chapel and church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Why do you think they were described as a gentleman or a lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think it\rquote s the way they conducted themselves, they way they dressed, they had clean habits and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you remember seeing a policeman around when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I do. I do. I think they had wonderful influence in those days. Policemen walked - walked around or rode on bicycles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Generally they were very good - very co-operative again. There was the odd policeman who might get a bit bumptious if some kids were playing him up and that sort of business and chase \lquote em, but I - I never saw a policeman strike anyone with his }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 truncheon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 , he might get them by the scruff of the neck and give \lquote em a shaking and tell them to behave themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You respected the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You thought he treated people quite well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Generally, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 The house you went to in 1905?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 In Vivian Street, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, they came to collect the rent weekly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well the - when - where we w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 ere he was - well he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 was not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 bad at all, he was a pretty good fellow, he was one of those fellows that had speculated a bit in his day you know in his way, b
uilt these new houses, which would be built in those days for about a hundred and twenty pounds for a six roomed house. Fix the rent accordingly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, I do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 They - extremely careful, they couldn\rquote 
t go in for a lot of - holidays or anything like that, they could never have holidays and going away for holidays in those days
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any feelings about it as a child or did you accept it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
More - accepted and then felt I would like to see these other people - in the - as I say, in the early days of the trains and excursions to Sailor Peak and the seaside resorts somebody would like to go on a trip to Skegness and tho
se places and they regarded that as a great occasion, to go out and take the children in they could as well on the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well of course he was reasonably fortunate in the sense that he\rquote 
d get his - sick pay from the Oddfellows, before the National Health panel scheme or anything else like that came in and that did help a bit. And then his later years of course the other members of the family were at work and that - that
 helped out of course, the brothers and sisters that were working then, after I\rquote d got married and left home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did he have any long illnesses, you\rquote ve told me about his periods of unemployment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, he - he died at seventy-three, seventy-four and he
 had an operation in that Grobey Road hospital at Leicester, this lung operation, there was no T.B. or anything, something here in the lung, I forget the name what they call it now. We used to go and visit him out there and - he was - out at Grobey Road, 
then they brought him back to the Manor hospital here, this Derby hospital and then this sort of thing broke down and we were called in a hurry and he sort of more or less bled to death.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you ever get help from the Guardians or the Parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Not at the time when he was victimized by the firm but in later years he occasionally went down for some Poor Law Assistance. In later years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Can you remember how they treated you, did you ever come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, no I never had to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you remember if you had any feelings about your father having to go for charity to the Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well I did - I - I - I can remember him in his early days concerned about a national scheme, a national insurance, 
national health scheme. To cover this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any feelings about it as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
No. I thought something of that kind was necessary for the country in those days because there were so many people and - when I say they went in the friendly society there was only a small percentage that went into those things and they\rquote 
d got nothing when they were ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 If there was someone in the district who people disapproved of very strongly was there any way in which they showed it, was anyone ever mad
e to leave the district because of the playing of rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well - as far as I can recollect there was - in the district where I lived there was little or nothing of that. But in other areas, on the Ashton Road, what we call the old Nun Street whi
ch has now been modernized and three or four storey type flats, one of the earlier - earlier - Kings Mead ward it was called - was pulled down by the Labour council and rebuilt and everything - there was a lot of that at weekends. And that\rquote 
s when the police used to go three of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was anyone made to leave the district because they were misbehaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think so. If it was found they were running a corrupt place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who would make them leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Probably the landlord. By pressure from the - from the tenants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were you given lessons by your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, by the schoolteachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Originally four and a half years old. Four years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What time did you go in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Nine o\rquote clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Half past four - four thirty, sometimes a little later on about five o\rquote clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So you started all day at the age of four?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. That\rquote s right. Two hours for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What kind of school was it, a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It was a church school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And it was a d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 y school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was it boys only or mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Nixed. Mixed school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Walked it from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How long did it take?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It was about - ten minutes or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did anyone go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh when I was young, yes. Yes. I\rquote 
m just trying to think now who went with me, probably an older cousin who lived near us I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you come home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you think of school, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well generally I liked it, sometimes you got a bit - certain subjects probably that you - you felt a bit bored with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Generally pretty good, it was a mixed school in the sense that there was men and women teachers at the school. The headmaster was a man.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did the teachers }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 emphasise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  certain things as being important in life, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well you\rquote d be given a - a - you\rquote 
d have to stay on at school and write out two or three pages of lines. Sort of - sort of punishment. Occasionally the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were the girls treated the same as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, but I don\rquote t think they had the cane, I think they had to stay behind and write their composition, whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 For what sort of offences would you be punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well - sort of keep kicking up a noise at the back of the class or not taking the proper attention of the - what the teacher was saying and - not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 being}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  with it as it were, not being - interest as you should have been in the - in the subject.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. Yes. We used to have a report, a quarterly report you know - in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, occasionally, a
bout once a year there was some function on when the parents - not in my first years at school but about 1912 time and so on. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Generally, yes, in that area, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did the teachers ever single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
There appeared to be that fear occasionally by some teachers and some children, but generally, I must say in my case down there, they were pretty fair, they had a very goo
d - two - the two headmasters I - that I was under were very decent people altogether, particularly the last one. Very interested in sport and swimming and that kind of thing and he insisted and encouraged the - the - the boys particularly and the girls i
n the school to take these lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, there was one or two occasionally who - would do something in the class, probably to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 interrupt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  a lad - probably flirting and elastic at something - I had that o
n one or two occasions, turned round and shouted at the lad - the lad at the back of the school and then you were fetched out by the schoolteacher and given three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 storks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 . On one occasion when I was treated like that I was the - the victim and I was quite innocent of what happened, which of course often happened in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there any gangs of boys for particular age groups or if they came from a special district or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, no real gangs, they used to have the little do
minant types that were there you know, those days. Little bosses in their own way. Many of them there in those days they were so poor they used to go and deliver morning papers some of them, that kind of thing, to help their parents through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
No, if they were - if they were from the point of view of sport, football and that kind of thing, if they were rather weak, then the teachers understood it and they allowed them to stay in school and read -
 or do something to occupy their time or even the swimming business as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you go on to another school afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How old were you when you left there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you have stayed longer if you\rquote d had the opportunity?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 After you left school did you take part in part time education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. I - I went for a book keeping course at one of the evening schools, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you have any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 regrets}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, I think we were treated generally -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You think you benefited from attending school don\rquote t you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And then after I\rquote d left the school I went to the evening classes for the - course of book keeping. About 19 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 While you were still at school did you have any part time jobs or any means or earning regular pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, not really except in this case the person concerned asked me if I\rquote 
d like to deliver the Liberal Monthly in the area, there was about eighty or a hundred copies I think it was, and I said yes, and I got sixpence a month of delivering it. Sixpence a month, yes. And I carried on for some time. Probably \lquote 
til I started work properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you describe this as a regular job did you actually do it every month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Every month, yes. Yes. I did it for about a year or eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You got it on your own did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well someone - I think the person concerned were - were neighbours not far way, her husband was interested in that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You had to deliver these leaflets every month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 That\rquote s right. It was a small little publication - monthly publication.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have to do it on a particular day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, a certain time of the month they came in - you know, come in from the printers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What were you paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Sixpence.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any feelings about it as a wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. Of course sixpence then you see - if you were getting a penny a week when you were younger you were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you keep that sixpence yourself or did you give any to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I - I don\rquote t - I can\rquote 
t just remember, I might have done - bought my mother some sweets or something of that kind when I got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you work with anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, there was just - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It was such a small job it wouldn\rquote t alter your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, it was done in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 evenings or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  weekends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you feel about the job itself, did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And they treated you all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any other part time job before you left school or just that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you get your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well I - first full time job, yes, well - whether I was told of it by some friend or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 school friend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  or not I don\rquote t know but I - heard of a
 job going at a shop in St Peters Street, Derby, name of John D. Eaton. John D. Eaton, they were pawnbrokers, jewelers and clothiers. And I as appointed to that job. I stayed there for four years. It was an interesting job and a - the first war was on of 
course I remember, we had two or three zeppelin raids over Derby at the time and we - wed got a big basement there which we took refuge in because we worked until about nine o\rquote 
clock at night in those days you know. And ten on Saturdays, oh yes, yes. Then later in 1915 there was a bit of an improvement in the Shops Act conditions and - we did finish at about seven or eight o\rquote 
clock and nine on Saturdays, but - first seven or eight months I was there until ten o'clock - half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 en}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid556407\charrsid15021746  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 closing all the shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What time did you get there in the morning?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well on pledge day, Monday, seven thirty. Seven thirty until nine o\rquote 
clock. And I went on still even after the shop - the day hours had - had improved somewhat, it went on and we still met at seven thirty in the morning, \lquote 
cos the people used to come down early, as soon as they were getting the children off to school, and bring their pledges in and - in many cases - some people would bring neighbours pledges as well, use a pram to bring the parcels and that 
kind of thing down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What hours did you work on a Saturday?
