\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Half past seven in the morning \lquote til ten at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have a half day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Wednesday. Wednesday was a half day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What time did you finish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 One o\rquote clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 One week. After me first twelve months there, one week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What exactly did you have to do in this job when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well in the - in the - in the - I was - in the first months or the first twelve months for instance I was in the pawnbroker department, writing out the pledges tickets, making up the - them up in parcels, and putting the duplicate ticket on with a n
umber and taking it - \lquote em upstairs to the racks where they kept all the pledges you know. There was no proper lift in those days but there was one of those rather - you know - pull up sort of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  operated thing, with this - with a sort of a s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13860319\charrsid15021746 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 ck, leather sack where you could drop certain things - down or tie them to the rope and drop them, if it was clothing or soft things like that. But other - other things of course you couldn\rquote 
t. I wrote the tickets out, put them on, and then we used to charge them I think it was a ha\rquote penny - a ha\rquote penny for the first two shilling pledges, the ticket, either a hapenny or a penny, I can\lquote 
t just remember now. In fact I said it was one of the fair - having that experience, that was one of the fairest ways if you\rquote re short of m
oney temporarily the best thing was to go on pledging, many people did, people who were in business in the town centre - used to pledge their gold Alberts and bracelets and watches and that kind of thing you know. Yes. The rate of interest was very low th
at we charged.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So you were on the clerical 1 side more than anything when you first went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Yes, and then on the serving side later I was - I served both in the outfitters, in the mens department, mens clothing - mens clothing mainly, and - 
they also had a carpet - carpet room upstairs and then I - and finally I went into the jewellery department. There was three separate shops you see. The jewellery department, very interesting, the war was well on then, it was about 1916 - \rquote 
17, I remember many of the troops of those days coming over on leave and purchasing one of the old type Ingersoll watches with a - a cover on you know that - to protect the glass, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What were you paid when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 When I first started, five shillings a seek.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you feel anything about that wage, did you think it a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Yes, as I found out at the time, apart from the Co-op - which I think they paid their - errand boys and starters about five or six shillings a week, a number of fir
ms in Derby only paid three and six or four shillings, not - not similar type of firm but some of the shops and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. Yes. Most of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What was it spent on, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Help in the household requirements. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you get on with the people you worked with in the pawnbrokers shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Very well. Yes, very well. There was a staff of about three in the pawnbrokers department, two or three in the mens clothin
g department, and two - three in the jewellers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well there was a manager in charge of the place then, and the employer actually John D. Eaton, he came from Sheffield, and he had about five - three or four shops i
n Sheffield, one at Ilkeston and another somewhere else in Derbyshire, I just forget where now, the one at Ilkeston and a second one in Derby in Queen Street where the big public baths are now. Well that was pawnbroking only. There was no clothing or jewe
llers up there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So did you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Oh he came over most weeks on a Friday by train from Sheffield, had a - one of the old cab - growlers - to bring him down from the Derby Midland station and - to - dropped him off at the shop in St Peters
 Street. And he used to pay us out and he had a big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 strong room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 there obviously because they had a lot of valuable stuff they had to keep, not - not a small safe, a big room about the size of this where they put some of he pledges of that kind and they had
 us cash and everything else in there on a short table and used to pay us out on - board on Friday. All the staff used to go into and draw their wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any feelings about him as an employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - you - you didn\rquote t get much association with him - he was - so he\rquote 
d got all these other shops on and he was - a rotund type of - late middle aged man when I knew him and - when he died he left the rest of the employees some short - small sums of money up to a hundred pound and I'd just left 
in 1918 and he died in 1920 so - I didn\rquote t benefit from that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you feel about the work itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I enjoyed it generally, it was long hours as I say but - I was young enough then to sort of - take it, carry it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So on balance you rather liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did the job alter your attitude to school in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. No, I don\rquote 
t think so. I think most of the people who were older than me, they were more seniors, had had much the same kind of education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You said you worked at this place until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I went and I got a - started at Rolls Royce. Rolls Royce Nightingale Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - a friend of mine was at Rolls Royce and he suggested I go and try - where the wages were rather higher than they were at Eaton
\rquote s - that I go and - make an application which I did and I was appointed. In an office there. In an office, that\rquote s right, yes, dealing with sub-contract work, checking stuff and all that. 
And in the works, I was - had - I was - put into an office but I had to move about the works checking all this stuff you know, materials for the aircraft engine of those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What would the job be called, would it have a name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 The job I was ac
tually doing later after - after a few months, I was there two - just over two years - was called the replacement of defective work. And it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was it basically clerical?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well it was partly clerical but my job was to go round the factory in the va
rious bays where there was the turning and - and drilling and all that kind of thing going on and if there was same - so many parts, particular parts, say fifty or - or a hundred, and some if it was scrap, say twenty-five or thirty were scrapped, I had to
 check that up and then go and order from the steel section sufficient of that kind of metal to replace those parts. Very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What hours did you work in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - first of all six o\rquote clock in the morning, it was works - works staff I was on. Six in the morning \lquote 
til half past five at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, we worked Saturdays then, Saturdays I think we worked \lquote til - twelve or twelve thirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you work Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Only if necessary, only if it was urgent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 The half day then would be on the Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 That\rquote s right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any holidays with pay in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, I think they were there introducing their early holidays even - even with the works - the works men as well, and I think t
hey got a weeks holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What were you paid when you first started there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Round about a pound a week. Eighteen shillings or a pound a week, I couldn\rquote 
t just remember now fully, I was only eighteen of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you feel that was a fair wage or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well, I thought it was an improvement on - on some of what I\rquote d heard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you give any of this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. I give her - I should think at lest half of it, I - of course I had bus or tram fares to pay to get to t
he job, it was a fair distance away from where I lived, some three miles or more. Three or four miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And this money would be spent on household requirements as before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, yes, yes. And I got to the stage then when I was beginning to buy my own suits - my own clothes, clothing, of course I\rquote 
d got to save for that.
