\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Very well generally. Very well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 An your employer, did you ever know your employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - Roolls of course, I think he died around about 1912 - \rquote 
14 - Henry Rolls but the - Henry Royce rather, Royce was there for some years, many years afterwards. He used to come down to the firm fairly frequently - from Manchester I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Then he went to live on the coast somewhere didn\rquote t he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Yes. Of course they started up at Manchester you know. Yes. And a lot of the Lancashire Manchester type people came down with them when they started Derby 1910 or 1909, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 But as an employer he would be somewhat far removed from yourself wouldn\rquote t he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you ever have any feeling about how he treated you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well - I think the general feeling of the - both the staff and those in the works was that they were - working with a new typ
e of firm, a new development and they were being paid reasonable, what they thought in those days was reasonable pay compared with some of the other engineering type of firms in some parts of the town and the country. That - probably came out of the small
 bonus they got.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any feelings about him yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well I think we all felt that - during the first world war we were old enough to remember it - that they\rquote d done a good job, they
\rquote d done a great job in producing this type of aircraft which had been used in the war and probably helped to shorten it in some way, if we can say that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you feel about the work that you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh it was interesting. Interesting, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, I liked it, yes, generally. Except when I was - I\rquote d worked for a short time in the drop forge, they\rquote 
d got an office there, a small sort of glass place like a small greenhouse where the manager of the department, the drop forge, and myself worked with the
 records and all kinds of things. And the noise and the fumes was terrific from that in those days you know, steel and - and banging hammers and all that - tremendous hammers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So you were there for two years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What did you do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well of course there came the slump. In a minor way similar to the one that they\rquote 
ve had in recent months. The aircraft production was reduced considerably, the war was over, war had been over two years, and the production of the two aircraft e
ngines which were then known as the one-ninety horsepower and the 250 horsepower they were - cut down production considerably of that and went back then onto the car - for production of cars again, they still produced the cars at Derby of course in those 
days. And - after a time they began to recover, fairly slowly. In the meantime I\rquote d been unemployed for nine months and finally got a job at the British Celanese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You were out of work for nine months in 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Out of work for nine months, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Then you went to work for British Celanese?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 British Celanese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 In what sort of capacity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Again one of the departments where they were making the early plastics. I was in the office of the department. And of course - I\rquote 
m not allowed to say this but many of the people there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 suffering}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 from the fumes, the benzol and diesel fumes in those days you know, working in that atmosphere. It did affect your health, particularly if you\rquote re getting old, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5988290\charrsid15021746 I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  was young but it did me and others because we were breathing in - all this stuff there and - benzine fumes and that, because I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 to work}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  quite a bit inside the department where they were producing this thing although we\rquote d got an office - a one storey wooden type of office - in the grounds of the works.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Until 1936.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Then what did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Appointed agent of Derby - Secretary Agent of Derby Labour party. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How long did you remain in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well, just under thirty years - twenty-nine years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Until your retirement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I gave in my notice - well, I - I wasn\rquote 
t well, I was - not too good at all after the 1964 general election. It was the - the strain and everything, and I - had about a fortnights holiday, went back and told the execut
ive in the October November rather that I thought it was time I give me notice. They were very sorry of course to hear it but I - I could have gone on another eight or nine months to sixty-five. However I give my notice and they asked me stand on until th
ey could get someone to succeed me and - I had to carry on until the following May municipal elections, although I\rquote d given me notice in in the November, because the person who was going to follow me came from Grimsby and he\rquote 
d got to stop behind and do the local elections in Grimsby and clear up afterwards, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Looking aback on your working life this last one was your biggest single job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 It was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Looking back on this job and the others you did would you have preferred another type of occupation do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well I\rquote d be - I\rquote d got extremely interested in the - Labour party and in the - working c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5988290\charrsid15021746 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 ass Socialist movement and felt that I could do something by taking that job on to improve the conditions that I\rquote d hoped to see improved when
 I was much younger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So there wouldn\rquote t have been much that you\rquote d rather have done?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No. Not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of the jobs that you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, in the - in the case of the - Labour pa
rty I took courses under the N.C.L. National Council of Labour Courses - postal courses, before I took over as Agent on - Economics - history, geography - and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And how did evening classes when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Evening classes in the early twenties at one of the Derby evening schools. Did two years for book keeping. For accountancy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So in fact you did quite a bit of training in your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes, I joined the trade union when I went to Rolls Royce in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What union would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Clerks. Known then as the National Union of Warehousemen and Clerks. Yes. Yes. That\rquote s right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you take part in any of its activities then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5988290\charrsid15021746 attended}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
 the meetings 
of the branch, there were several branches there of course, there was the - it was a large firm in those days, Rolls Royce you know. Yes, I attended the meetings, that was as I say 1918, 1919 I joined the I.L.P. Went to their monthly meetings. Yes. In 192
0 I - became - of course individual membership didn\rquote t grow until later. \lquote 
Til after 1910 time you know, and I joined the ward in which I lived, still down there, in the party, the Labour party then, and took an active part in the ward activities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different, round about the time when you started at Rolls Royce?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think there appeared to be a - a tendency towards at, at Roolls Royce anyway. The staff people - had quite an interest in t
he job they were doing as well as the workmen, whether they were skilled workmen or labourers - or unskilled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you feel that there was a division of interest between the workers, were you conscious of any division of interest among workers?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 W
ell I think there was always that - that element - that attitude that the staff are somebody above us you know in those days but I think it began to break down after - in the 1920\rquote s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What about the division between trained craftsmen and other workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Worked out generally well, the trained ones and the unskilled ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You didn\rquote t think there was a great division between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I don\rquote t think so, no, they - of course the wages were higher for the trades people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well I think that - you were here to do a job and you were here to earn - a good living wage if we could, and I think we took an interest in the job because of that. And in certain aspects 
of certain jobs there was something that appealed to you more than others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Oh yes, until I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
No. No, except that when I got into my sort of late teens I was very keen on - on - theatre. Operas and the early musical comedies and - Gilbert and Sillivan and that kind of thing and I used to try and get to those - whenever I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your relationship with your brothers and sisters alter in any way when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, I don\rquote t think so, I think they looked upon me as the older brother because - yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you spend your Sunday any differently after you started work, in regard to the church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, I don\rquote t think - in the later years, in the 20\rquote 
s, I used to usually go to the meetings on Sunday evening. The I.L.P. used to have regular Sunday meetings in Derby and had some of the leading lights of the I.L.P. in those days including Jimmy Maxton and those people, coming down to Derby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You had an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And you attended the big open air meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. There were a lot and of course there we
re indoor meetings in the - in the wintertime. Usually on the Co-op premises, they had a small hall and a large hall, yes. David Kirkwood and - all characters of those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What were your views, you were a supporter of the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Why did you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well because I thought the Labour party when it was formed had been formed for that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 purpose}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 , to improve the conditions and standard of the - working class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was your wife interested in politics before you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Her mother was, her mother and father were very interested. Her mother particularly in the Co-operative side the father in the N.U.R. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So your wife also was brought up in a political organization background?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. She was, yes. Yes she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Which she still retains now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh that\rquote s right. She - she became a member - \lquote 
course she lived away from near where I lived, she lived in another ward at Derby and she became a member of that ward in her early twenties. Took a part in it with her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Neither of you had a vote before 1919 did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 \rquote 21 - \rquote 22 was the first time I was able to vote. Act - that new act came in in 1921 didn\rquote t it. They didn\rquote 
t have it for the 1919 election after the first war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You\rquote d be under age anyway then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 -Under twenty-one that\rquote s right. \rquote 21, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were you a member of a political party at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes, I was a member of the Derwent ward Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You were an individual member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you work for the party at elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Do you know whether your wife did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think she did in the way of writing the literature, writing out local election literature and that kind of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You don\rquote t know whether she was a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 She was a member, I\rquote m pretty sure. Yes, and she - she helped her mother was active in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11739596\charrsid15021746 women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746  section of the ward in which she lived and they were in sections helped the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Were there any other political activities you took part in other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well we used - no, I don\rquote 
t think there was because we used to have meetings on the market place, open air meetings and used to have meetings of the I.L.P. Then there was the union branch meetings of course. And friendly society of which I was a member, the Oddfellows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 What was the Labour party Cycling club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Carion Club, that\rquote s right, they had a Clarion Club in Derby in those days, I don\rquote t - wasn\rquote 
t particularly a member of the Clarion Club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you spend your spare time in different ways now you were a young working man? You said you started to go to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. And in the summer time of course walking was - where I lived we were right on the end of the town and were soon out in the country. 
Long walks in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 So you\rquote d go for walks in the country in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Or to the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Who would you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well there was three of us, one was killed in the first war, one of - the oldest of the thr
ee, there were three of us friends, been pretty well at school at the same time, same years and we used to go along to these - not every week, but when there was something special at the Derby Grand Theatre. It was one of the largest in the country - outs
ide London. Yes, in those days, one of the largest stage - largest stages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls, at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 No, mainly boys I think. Fellows that I knew we were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you meet them, where would you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Association through the - the area where we lived. Some of us had been at school together, the same school, and then again linking up with some of the friends we\rquote d met up with in the I.L.P. and the party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you ever bring any of you friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Oh yes. On occasions, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have any special friend at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well there was a cousin of mine who - called up - another one called up for the first war, around a bout a year older than me - and then another -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Was this a boy or a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Boy. Two schoolfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Where would you go with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Well in the early twenties we joined a tennis club. And at certain times - at weekends - Saturdays and - Saturday afternoon or Saturday evening we\rquote d go and play tennis, in the - in the season - grass courts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did your parents expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Well not - I mean if I was going to the theatre of course I should tell them, it might be ten or eleven o\rquote 
clock before it finished in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 
Not - not generally, no. No, there was - no point in staying out late. But - if we had to walk say in the late war years and the wars immediately afterwards there was a fairly long distance to walk from the theatre to where I lived and - about two miles.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 You were married when you were twenty-nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Well I should be twenty-eight actually, I was twenty - married in July as I was twenty-nine in the September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How long had you known your wife then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Since 1923. Five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 How did you meet, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 I think it was out with some of my friends, one of them knew one of her friends and we met then. So - some of her girlfriends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5077811 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 And she was local was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4794022 HR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5065330\charrsid15021746 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }}